INSERT INTO `tips` VALUES (113,'Bus/Walk','💁 Talk about the speed you are going to learn fast and slow','Tell your child, we are going to learn \"Fast, slow, and stop today!\" and label each of these speeds on your trip.'),(114,'Bus/Walk','💁 Talk about the speed you are going to learn fast and slow','Use gestures and the speed of your voice to help our child learn fast, slow, and stop.'),(115,'Bus/Walk','💁 Talk about the speed you are going to learn fast and slow','Ask your child, \"Are we going fast or slow?\"'),(116,'Bus/Walk','Watch the stop lights to learn about colors','Point to the stop light, and say, \"look it\'s green, green means go!\", \"the light turned yellow, yellow means slow down!\" and \"the light is red, red means stop!\"'),(117,'Bus/Walk','Watch the stop lights to learn about colors','Watch the cars with your child, and say, \"The blue car stopped on red!\"'),(118,'Bus/Walk','Watch the stop lights to learn about colors','If there are no stoplights around, talk about the street signs.'),(119,'Bus/Walk','Find the street signs to talk about shapes, colors, and letters','Tell your child, \"We are going to have fun looking for street signs!\"'),(120,'Bus/Walk','Find the street signs to talk about shapes, colors, and letters','Look for street signs as you go for a walk, and point them out for your child'),(121,'Bus/Walk','Find the street signs to talk about shapes, colors, and letters','Describe the shape, the color, and the letters on the sign.'),(122,'Bus/Walk','Let\'s talk 💁about car sounds!','Tell your child, \"We are going to watch cars! Cars go vroom vroom! What sound do cars make?\" Imitate 🔄 the noise your child makes.'),(123,'Bus/Walk','Let\'s talk 💁about car sounds!','Say, \"Car horns go beep beep! What sound do car horns make?\"  Wait 3 seconds for your child to respond.'),(124,'Bus/Walk','Let\'s talk 💁about car sounds!','Imitate 🔄 the noise your child makes. Noises are fun for babies and big kids to learn!'),(125,'Bus/Walk','🏆 First - Then Challenge','Preparing your child for where you are going helps your child know what to expect.'),(126,'Bus/Walk','🏆 First - Then Challenge','Tell your child, \"First we will go over a bridge. Then we will go under a bridge. Then we will go home!\"'),(127,'Bus/Walk','🏆 First - Then Challenge','Help your child find places you pass along the way. Label 💁 the places again. \"Look, we are going over a... Next we will go under a... Then we will go home!\"'),(128,'Bus/Walk','Let\'s look at the lines on the road','Point to the lines on the road and say, \"Look, at the yellow lines on the road!'),(129,'Bus/Walk','Let\'s look at the lines on the road','Talk about the different types of yellow lines on the road. \"There are two yellow lines here. These are dotted lines. These are short lines.\"'),(130,'Bus/Walk','Let\'s look at the lines on the road','Say, \"The yellow lines on the road help cars and buses know where to go!\"'),(131,'Bus/Walk','As you go by houses talk about the numbers on each house 💁','Label 💁, \"Each house has numbers! Look, that house has the numbers 4-2-3-1.\"'),(132,'Bus/Walk','As you go by houses talk about the numbers on each house 💁','Ask your child, \"Can you point to where the numbers are on another house?\" When your child points, say, \"Yes, those are numbers they are 5-4-2-3.\" Give positive attention, and say \"Great job!\" 👏'),(133,'Bus/Walk','As you go by houses talk about the numbers on each house 💁','If your child doesn\'t point or look, say, \"Look, there are the numbers!\"'),(134,'Bus/Walk','Learn about BIG and small by talking about the buildings you see','As you pass by different buildings 💁 comment and label, \"Look, there is a BIG building. This building is tall!\"'),(135,'Bus/Walk','Learn about BIG and small by talking about the buildings you see','Label another building and say, \"Look, this building is small!\" Ask your child, \"why is this building big?\" Why questions are hard for babies and young kids. Enjoy your child\'s response and tell them why.'),(136,'Bus/Walk','🏆 Street Safety Challenge','Safety when crossing the street is important for all children to learn.'),(137,'Bus/Walk','🏆 Street Safety Challenge','Before crossing the street, 💁say \"Let\'s stop and look both ways for cars!\" Look and point one way. Wait for your child to look too. Say \"I don\'t see any cars here!\"'),(138,'Bus/Walk','🏆 Street Safety Challenge','Look and point the other way. Say, \"Look there is a car! That means we need to wait!\"'),(139,'Bus/Walk','🏆 Street Safety Shape Challenge','While waiting at a stoplight, point to the stoplight in front of you.'),(140,'Bus/Walk','🏆 Street Safety Shape Challenge','Say, 💁 \"Look, it\'s a stoplight! The stoplight is a rectangle. A rectangle has four sides.\" Count the sides of the rectangle with your child.'),(141,'Bus/Walk','🏆 Street Safety Shape Challenge','Ask your child, \"Do you see any other shapes?\"'),(142,'Bus/Walk','🏆 Street Safety Shape Challenge','Point to and label other shapes surrounding the area.'),(143,'Bus/Walk','🏆 Street Safety Color Challenge: Find 3 Different Colors!','Talk about the stoplight colors. If you don\'t run into a stoplight, talk about different street signs.'),(144,'Bus/Walk','🏆 Street Safety Color Challenge: Find 3 Different Colors!','Say, 💁 \"The stoplight is red. It means we need to stop.\" Ask your child, \"What does red mean?\" Pause for several moments to give your child a chance to answer.'),(145,'Bus/Walk','🏆 Street Safety Color Challenge: Find 3 Different Colors!','Remind your child what each color means. Say, 💁  \"The red light means stop!\"'),(146,'Bus/Walk','Stop, Talk, and Listen! ','Talk about the positions of colors on a stoplight. Say, 💁 \"Look! The green light is above the yellow light.\"'),(147,'Bus/Walk','Stop, Talk, and Listen! ','Quiz your child by giving choices👈 👉 , \"Is the green light above or below the yellow light?\"'),(148,'Bus/Walk','Stop, Talk, and Listen! ','Try fill in the blank activities ⏳. Say,  \"The red light is below the ______.\" Mix up your questions to expose your child to new language.'),(149,'Bus/Walk','Talk about all the sounds you hear','When out and about in the community, there are many different sounds that we hear. Sounds are a fun way to interact with your child.'),(150,'Bus/Walk','Talk about all the sounds you hear','Talk 💁about the sounds that you hear, \"I hear the car brakes go squeak squeak!\"'),(151,'Bus/Walk','Talk about all the sounds you hear','Ask your child, \"What do you hear? Repeat 🔄 back the correct sound your child is making, \"That\'s right, the brakes go squeak squeak!\"'),(152,'Bus/Walk','Tell your child a story about them','To keep your child interested while you travel tell 💁them a story about when they were younger.'),(153,'Bus/Walk','Tell your child a story about them','Talk about what made them happy during the story. For example, \"When you were little we took you to your cousins, and you kept smiling the whole time!\"'),(154,'Bus/Walk','Tell your child a story about them','Telling stories is a fun way to interact and talk with your child, and is important for babies too!'),(155,'Bus/Walk','Let\'s learn about all the amazing ways we can move!','Talking about our actions and the way our body moves is a fun way to interact with your child'),(156,'Bus/Walk','Let\'s learn about all the amazing ways we can move!','For example, say 💁 \"I\'m clapping my hands, let me see you clap!\" Praise your child for clapping, if your child does not clap, help them, and then praise 👏.'),(157,'Bus/Walk','Let\'s learn about all the amazing ways we can move!','Try other movements like waving, nodding, pointing, jumping.'),(158,'Bus/Walk','Have fun observing what your child smiles and laughs at ','As you walk around watch 👀 for when your child smiles and listen for their laughter.'),(159,'Bus/Walk','Have fun observing what your child smiles and laughs at ','Label 💁 what they are smiling at, \"You must like it when I make silly voices!\"'),(160,'Bus/Walk','Have fun observing what your child smiles and laughs at ','Write down or remember what your child smiled at. This helps you to know what your child is interested in, and how to make your child smile on your next outing.'),(161,'General Store','🏆 Mirror Challenge','Tell your child, \"We are going to have fun finding mirrors today!\"'),(162,'General Store','🏆 Mirror Challenge','When you see a mirror, point and say, \"We found a mirror!\"'),(163,'General Store','🏆 Mirror Challenge','Look in the mirror together and talk about what you see. Imitate the faces and sounds your child makes.'),(164,'General Store','Search for things that spin: wheels, food warmers, drink machines, etc. ','Try to find 3 things that spin or turn during your trip!'),(165,'General Store','Search for things that spin: wheels, food warmers, drink machines, etc. ','Show your child the spinner and ask, \"Why does it spin?\"'),(166,'General Store','Search for things that spin: wheels, food warmers, drink machines, etc. ','\"Why\" questions are hard for babies and young children. Enjoy how your child responds, and then tell the answer.'),(167,'Grocery','🏆 Choice Challenge','Give you child a choice  👈 👉  on each aisle of the store you walk down.'),(168,'Grocery','🏆 Choice Challenge','Hold out the 2 choices as you label them.'),(169,'Grocery','🏆 Choice Challenge','If your child doesn\'t answer, say \"How about the...\" and move on.'),(170,'Grocery',' 👈 👉 Choices make a savvy shopper! ','Your child learns how to make smart choices by watching you and can begin to learn words that will help with decisions later.'),(171,'Grocery',' 👈 👉 Choices make a savvy shopper! ','Vocalize choices  👈 👉  you are making as you shop: \"Should I get the cereal that costs $2 or $4?\"'),(172,'Grocery',' 👈 👉 Choices make a savvy shopper! ','Then, share your decision with your child: \"The $2 cereal costs less. I\'ll get the cheaper one.\"'),(173,'Grocery Store','Talk about the sounds you hear at the cash register','Tell you child, \"Let\'s listen to the sounds that we hear!\"'),(174,'Grocery Store','Talk about the sounds you hear at the cash register','Say 💁, \"I hear a beep. They are scanning our food!\"'),(175,'Grocery Store','Talk about the sounds you hear at the cash register','Ask your child, \"What sound do you hear?\"'),(176,'Grocery Store','Talk about the sounds you hear at the cash register','Imitate 🔄 the sound that your child makes, and say, \"Yes, I hear the beep too!\"'),(177,'Grocery Store','🏆Open and Close Challenge','Talk to your child about 💁 how the doors to the gorcery store go open and close.'),(178,'Grocery Store','🏆Open and Close Challenge','Use your arms and hands to gesture what open and close mean. Imitate 🔄 how your child gestures open/close.'),(179,'Grocery Store','🏆Open and Close Challenge','While in the store look for other things that open and close (e.g., freezer doors, bulk goods containers, cash register) and label 💁 these for your child.'),(180,'Grocery store','Talk to your child about how two grocery items go together to make a recipe','Pick up two items from your cart used in a recipe.'),(181,'Grocery store','Talk to your child about how two grocery items go together to make a recipe','Show them to your child and label 💁 one item (e.g., \"Jelly\"). Hold up the other item and wait for your child to look, point or label. When they answer, praise 👏 your child, and say, \"Yes, bread! Jelly and Bread help make sandwiches!\"'),(182,'Grocery store','Talk to your child about how two grocery items go together to make a recipe','At home, show your child the items when cooking with them.'),(183,'Grocery store','Fruits & Veggies, Yummy Yummy! ','Label fruits and vegetables along with their colors. Say, 💁 \"I see a red apple. What colors do you see?\"'),(184,'Grocery store','Fruits & Veggies, Yummy Yummy! ','Search for new colors. Say 💁 \"I spy something yellow. Where is it? What fruit is it?\"'),(185,'Grocery store','Fruits & Veggies, Yummy Yummy! ','Notice how some items have multiple colors. Say 💁 \"This apple is red, but there are also green and yellow apples. Which kind of apples should we get today?\"'),(186,'Grocery store','Have fun watching 👀 what your child is interested in','Follow your child\'s lead 👀 today and watch where they want to go, what their eyes look at, what they point at, and what they smile at.'),(187,'Grocery store','Have fun watching 👀 what your child is interested in','For example, if your child is looking at the bananas, say 💁, \"I see you looking at the bananas!'),(188,'Grocery store','Have fun watching 👀 what your child is interested in','Following your child\'s lead 👀 is a great way to find out your child\'s interests.'),(189,'Library','Find the librarians and use new words to describe them!','Help your child find the librarians as you walk the library: \"Librarians wear badges. There\'s a librarian!\"'),(190,'Library','Find the librarians and use new words to describe them!','\"I see a librarian sitting at the checkout desk.\"'),(191,'Library','Find the librarians and use new words to describe them!','\"This librarian is pushing a cart of books.\"'),(192,'Library','Follow your child\'s lead 👀 to help them make book choices','When in the child\'s section, follow your child\'s lead 👀 to see which books they are excited to look at.'),(193,'Library','Follow your child\'s lead 👀 to help them make book choices','Pick up two of the books you notice your child interested in. Put out each book in front of your child.'),(194,'Library','Follow your child\'s lead 👀 to help them make book choices','Ask , \"Which one 👈 👉 would you like to take home?\" If your child doesn\'t make a choice, say, \"Let\'s pick ...\"'),(195,'Library','Count the pages of the books to help familiarize your child to numbers','Watch 👀 the books your child looks at to find books they are interested in.'),(196,'Library','Count the pages of the books to help familiarize your child to numbers','Open the book. Say, \"Let\'s look count the pages!\"'),(197,'Library','Count the pages of the books to help familiarize your child to numbers','Count the pages with your child.  Say, \"Wow this book is 10 pages!\"'),(198,'Library','Count the pages of the books to help familiarize your child to numbers','Ask your child, how many pages?  Wait 3 seconds to let your child answer by making noise or saying a word.'),(199,'Library','Count the pages of the books to help familiarize your child to numbers','💁 Say, \"Yay! It\'s 10  pages!\"'),(200,'Library','Use books to talk about heavy and light','Pick up two of your books, one small book and one large book.'),(201,'Library','Use books to talk about heavy and light','Say 💁, \"This book is big and heavy! Let\'s hold it!\" Help your child hold the book to feel \"heavy\". Show the other book. Say 💁\"This book is small and light! Let\'s hold it!\" Help your child hold the book to show to feel \"light\".'),(202,'Library','Use books to talk about heavy and light','Give a choice  👈 👉. Ask, \"Which book do you want to hold?\"'),(203,'Library','Talk about how quiet the library is','Tell your child, let\'s listen to how quiet it is!'),(204,'Library','Talk about how quiet the library is','Show your child what a whispering voice sounds like. Then say to your child, \"Let me hear you whisper!\"'),(205,'Library','Talk about how quiet the library is','Repeat 🔄 back the sound your child makes. If your child does not make a whispering sound, say, \"Oh, this is how we whisper!\" and talk in a whisper voice again.'),(206,'Library','How does a library work','Talk to your child about the process of checking out books'),(207,'Library','How does a library work','Say, \"We can only check out three books at a time. Let\'s count how many books we have.\" Count with your child'),(208,'Library','Search and find for books','What has your child been interested in lately?'),(209,'Library','Search and find for books','Remind your child of recent interests'),(210,'Library','Search and find for books','Talk to the librarian if you would like help'),(211,'Library','Find a Helper Challenge','Tell your child, \"Librarians are helpers. Where should we look for a librarian?\"'),(212,'Library','Find a Helper Challenge','If your child points, go in that direction. If not, give two choices of directions. \"Should we go this way or that way?\"'),(213,'Library','Find a Helper Challenge','Model how to say hi and/or wave to the librarian.'),(214,'Library','High, Low: How big can you go?','Pick a high book that is still within your child\'s reach. Say, \"I wonder if you can reach this book?\" If your child tries to reach talk about how big they are.'),(215,'Library','High, Low: How big can you go?','Pick a book on a low shelf and say: \"I don\'t know if I can reach that low. Can you help me?\"'),(216,'Library','High, Low: How big can you go?','You can help your baby by showing her how to pull on the books.'),(217,'Library','Book return time: Let\'s play delivery man!','Let your child pretend to be the delivery person. If you have a young baby, you can pretend as a team and model.'),(218,'Library','Book return time: Let\'s play delivery man!','As she delivers books to the drop box, ask questions: \"Where did the book go?\" \"What do you think happened to the book?\"'),(219,'Library','Book return time: Let\'s play delivery man!','Give a choice: \"Which book should do you want to put in next, the dog book or the food book?\"'),(220,'Library','Library Interview Fun','Let your child be the library expert! Ask questions and enjoy your child\'s responses.'),(221,'Library','Library Interview Fun','Babies respond with noises and gestures. You can talk back as if they used words.'),(222,'Library','Library Interview Fun','Examples: How many books do you think are in this library? How do you think the books get on the shelves? What do you think that machine is for? (point at a copier or computer)'),(223,'Park','Let\'s go on a scavenger hunt for the color green!','Tell your child, \"We are going to look for the color green today.\"'),(224,'Park','Let\'s go on a scavenger hunt for the color green!','As you walk outside, help your child by pointing to the tree, and saying, \"The tree is green!\"'),(225,'Park','Let\'s go on a scavenger hunt for the color green!','Label 💁something else that is green, and ask❓your child, \"What color is this?\"'),(226,'Park',' 🏆 Tree Challenge','Tell your child, \"We are going to look for trees today.\"'),(227,'Park',' 🏆 Tree Challenge','Help your child find the trees, and say, \"Trees have roots, let\'s touch the roots.\" Tell your child, \"Trees have a trunk, let\'s touch the trunk.\" After touching the trunk, ask your child, how does it feel?'),(228,'Park',' 🏆 Tree Challenge','Point to the leaves and branches, and say \"Trees have branches and leaves.\"'),(229,'Park','🏆 Letter Challenge','Find as many sticks as you can with your child. Say, \"We are going to make letters!\"'),(230,'Park','🏆 Letter Challenge','👀It can be motivating to pick letters in your child\'s name. Make the letter with the sticks. Say, \"Look! This is the letter \"A,\" \"A\" is in your name!\"'),(231,'Park','🏆 Letter Challenge','It\'s good to talk about letters with babies and big kids so they get familiar with the idea!'),(232,'Park','Let your child make choices 👈 👉 about which path to take ','Go on a walk with your child. Let your child make choices with which path to follow'),(233,'Park','Let your child make choices 👈 👉 about which path to take ','Ask your child and point, \"Should we go to the right 👉or to the left 👈\". Label 💁 your child\'s choice.'),(234,'Park','Let your child make choices 👈 👉 about which path to take ','If your child doesn\'t answer by pointing, looking, or talking, say \"How about we go (right or left)?\"'),(235,'Park','🏆 BIG and small challenge','Find various sizes of sticks. Put two sticks next to each other. Label 💁and point, \"Look, this one is BIG and this one is small.\" Use your arms and hands to gesture BIG and small.'),(236,'Park','🏆 BIG and small challenge','Get two more sticks and ask, \"Which one is BIG?\"'),(237,'Park','🏆 BIG and small challenge','Repeat 🔄 back your child\'s answer. If your child doesn\'t respond by pointing, or talking, say \"This stick is BIGGER.\"'),(238,'Park','Let\'s talk 💁about the textures at the park, and how they feel!','Search for trees, grass, bushes, and pinecones.'),(239,'Park','Let\'s talk 💁about the textures at the park, and how they feel!','Give your child a choice  👈 👉 , \"Should we look for trees or grass first?\" If your child doesn\'t answer by pointing, looking, or talking, say \"Let\'s look for trees!\"'),(240,'Park','Let\'s talk 💁about the textures at the park, and how they feel!','Let your child touch the objects you find, and talk about how it feels, \"The tree trunk feels rough.\" \"The grass feels soft!\"'),(241,'Park','Label emotions for your child as they play at the park','When you see your child make a sad or angry face label 💁 these.'),(242,'Park','Label emotions for your child as they play at the park','Tell your child, \"Your face tells me you are sad. You must not like the ...\"'),(243,'Park','Label emotions for your child as they play at the park','When your child is smiling or laughing say, \"Your face tells me you are happy. You must enjoy the swing!\"'),(244,'Park','Label emotions for your child as they play at the park','Labeling emotions helps children learn about their emotions and feelings.'),(245,'Park','Science: Let\'s learn about gravity and how fast things drop!','Look for a big and small acorn. Let your child help you find them. Say 💁, \"You found an acorn!\"'),(246,'Park','Science: Let\'s learn about gravity and how fast things drop!','Go the top of a slide. Ask your child, \"Which acorn will roll faster?\" Repeat back 🔄 what your child points to or says, \"You think the big one will go faster!\"'),(247,'Park','Science: Let\'s learn about gravity and how fast things drop!','Roll the acorns. Talk 💁 about what happened, \"You were right, the big one rolled faster!\"'),(248,'Park','🏆Hug Challenge','Hugs can help your child know how much you care about them.'),(249,'Park','🏆Hug Challenge','Look for something your child does that you are excited about or proud of. Praise 👏 by saying, \"I\'m so proud you for playing with your toy!\"'),(250,'Park','🏆Hug Challenge','Show your child how proud you are by giving them a big hug!'),(251,'Park','Enjoy talking about what you see','There are so many colors, shapes, and noises to talk about when at the park.'),(252,'Park','Enjoy talking about what you see','Take a look around and talk about what you see. \"I see a blue bird flying in the sky.\"'),(253,'Park','Enjoy talking about what you see','The more positive words a child hears the more you help them develop language!'),(254,'Restaurant','Ask \"which\" questions to keep your child involved','Ask \"Which dinner should I get?\" while pointing at the menu.'),(255,'Restaurant','Ask \"which\" questions to keep your child involved','Ask \"Which drink looks yummy?\" if there is a fountain drink dispenser.'),(256,'Restaurant','Ask \"which\" questions to keep your child involved','Ask \"Which table should we sit at?\" when finding a seat.'),(257,'Restaurant','Science: Let\'s learn about water','Get two extra cups and fill one cup full of ice, and fill one cup with 3 ice cubes and water. Tell your child, \"When ice gets warm it melts and becomes water.'),(258,'Restaurant','Science: Let\'s learn about water','Let your child feel the two cups to see which one feels colder. Label 💁 \"I think this one feels cold, brrr!\" Enjoy watching and 💁labeling which cup is melting faster.'),(259,'Waiting Room','💁 Clock and number fun','Find a clock. Say, \"Look at the clock. There are 12 numbers. Let\'s count!\" Count the numbers for your child.'),(260,'Waiting Room','💁 Clock and number fun','Then count with your child. Wait 3 seconds before counting the next number to let your child fill in the 